snippet.title: Future of Navajo Governance 2012, Panel 1: Histories of power, authority, and governance
snippet.description:
Panelists: Amber Crotty, Andrew Curley, Lloyd Lee. Discussant: Peter Iverson

When we talk through questions of government reform or development, we often do this in a way that incorporates many assumptions about governance, power, and authority into our conversations and analyses. But we fail to appreciate where these notions originate. Often they are taught and diffused to tribal peoples through colonial relationships. This has bearing on questions of sovereignty, executive authority, legislative authority, judicial powers, and fundamental laws.
